HEADWORD: Cachunde
<hw>Ca*chun"de</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A pastil or troche, composed of various aromatic
and other ingredients, highly celebrated in India as an antidote, and as
a stomachic and antispasmodic.</def>⟦br⟧
